A road accident in Bronkhorstspruit between a scholar transport taxi and a truck on 21 April that claimed the lives of 18 children and two adults has left families devastated.The Daily Vox spoke to the Masilela and Masuku families, who are still in shock. Mancoba Masuku remembers his six-year-old daughter, Buhle, who wanted to be a doctor.Phindile Masilela, who lost her 37-year-old brother, Mancani, and her nephews, Nkosinathi (16) and Ayanda (9), is angry: Each and every week we are losing our loved people, our families. Everyone, she said.Watch the video below: